  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "SEC1",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Transportation Execution Process"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Transportation Execution is the operational phase where planned shipments are physically transported from the source location to the destination. SAP TM manages execution activities such as dispatching, loading, departure, in-transit monitoring, proof of delivery and completion of Freight Orders."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC3",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "important",
      "title": "Key Concept",
      "content": "Planning creates Freight Orders; Transportation Execution performs the actual movement of goods."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC4",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Objectives of Transportation Execution"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC5",
      "type": "bullet-list",
      "items": [
        "Execute transportation plans",
        "Monitor shipment progress",
        "Track transportation events",
        "Manage transportation exceptions",
        "Provide shipment visibility",
        "Support proof of delivery",
        "Enable freight settlement"
      ]
    },
    {
