        "Improved customer communication",
        "Reduced transportation delays",
        "Better carrier coordination",
        "Accurate execution records",
        "Improved operational control"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC17",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "best-practice",
      "title": "Best Practice",
      "content": "Capture execution events in real time using mobile applications, GPS devices or carrier integration to maintain accurate shipment visibility."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC18",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "example",
      "title": "Real Project Example",
      "content": "A logistics provider integrated telematics with SAP TM to receive automatic arrival and departure events. Dispatchers could monitor more than 2,000 active shipments in real time without manual status updates."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC19",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "interview-tip",
      "title": "Interview Tip",
      "content": "Transportation Execution begins after the Freight Order is released. Remember the typical execution sequence: Loading -> Departure -> In Transit -> Delivery -> Proof of Delivery -> Completion."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC20",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "warning",
      "title": "Common Mistake",
      "content": "Execution is not limited to moving goods. It also includes event tracking, status management, proof of delivery and exception handling."
    },
    {
